Governors under the umbrella of Progressive Governors Forum (PGF) have revealed that governors elected on the party’s platform and the National Working Committee (NWC) are working together to resolve recurrent crisis within the APC. The body of APC governors also said that President Muhammadu Buhari has given them his firm commitment towards the survival of APC beyond 2023 when his tenure in office is expected to elapse. LEADERSHIP recalls that some prominent members of the APC had openly called for the removal of Comrade Adams Oshiomhole as the party’s national chairman. Speaking with newsmen in Abuja at the weekend, Jigawa state governor and the co-chairman of the PGF Governance Programme Steering Committee, Abubakar Badaru, stated that APC governors were doing all they can to ensure the party’s issues were resolved amicably within the shortest possible time. Responding to the outburst by the Ekiti state governor, Kayode Fayemi, that APC may not survive beyond Buhari’s tenure, the Jigawa state governor, when asked said: “On the survival of APC after President Buhari, the president made a commitment to the Governors that he will support us in anyway to make sure that the party survives and waxes stronger even after him.” On the crisis rocking the party, Badaru said Badaru said: “What I will have to say on the party is that the leadership of APC, Progressives Governors Forum (PGF) are working day and night to ensure that the issue is resolved and I assure you that Mr. President is also looking at the issue to make sure that the leadership crisis is resolved and it will be resolved in no time. We are working on it and God’s willing it will be over soon.”